news.title: WSB Real Estate Debt Fund II invests Rs 165 crore in Sowparnika Homes
news.para: Vimal Jangla on behalf of WSBREDF II said, "This funding shall facilitate the delivery of ~2,750 homes in mid-income and affordable housing category."

news.title: NOCs must to regularize construction under new impact few rule in Gujarat
news.para: ​The state urban development department has clarified that applications without no-objection certificates from Real Estate Regulatory Authority (RERA), Ahmedabad Fire and Emergency Services (AFES) and health department will be rejected.

news.title: Kochi corporation to extend deadline of Rajiv Awas Yojana project for fifth time
news.para: As per original schedule, the work should have been completed by 2018. Now, authorities are seeking the approval of the council to extend the deadline for the fifth time.

news.title: Telangana CM to meet district collectors to address Dharani woes
news.para: With complaints flooding from the public, farmers, political parties and even ruling party MLAs expressing fears of Dharani shadow on poll prospects, chief minister K Chandrasekhar Rao has now decided to address the concerns.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad: PCMC tells ward officers not to snap supply of property tax defaulters
news.para: The Pimpri Chinchwad civic body restored the connection within a few hours and now has issued a letter to its ward officers to refrain from snapping any more water connection.

news.title: Rajasthan housing board to sell flats at huge rebate to fund new luxury project
news.para: However, the board has also decided to sell 2,235 unsold flats in various projects constructed by it in the last 10 years at 25-50% discount to accommodate this project.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body's board okays transit-oriented development along RRTS corridor
news.para: The board decided to declare up to 1.5km on both sides of the rapid rail alignment as TOD zones, a move that would boost the real estate sector, and incorporate the same into the city’s Master Plan-2031.

news.title: Gurugram: Structural audit of 16 highrises over, report likely today
news.para: In the first week of August, the district administration finalised the four agencies for carrying out structural audits of 17 housing societies where residents alleged serious flaws in construction quality.

news.title: SIT arrests five more developers in Kalyan-Dombivli RERA scam
news.para: The SIT have booked 65 developers in case and earlier they had arrested 5 persons in this scam who had prepared forged documents making total arrest of 10 people in case so far.

news.title: ED may oppose plea to release assets of Omkar promoters
news.para: Recently, the court discharged Varma and Gupta, along with actor-businessman Sachin Joshi, in the money-laundering case in which these properties had been attached by ED.

news.title: Noida: FIR lodged against Country Colonisers' director for obstructing ED probe
news.para: ​The FIR has been lodged against Harmandeep Singh Kandhari, director of Mohali-based Country Colonisers Private Limited (CCPL), an associate company of the Wave Group, the officials said.

news.title: Three of China's biggest banks to provide support for builders
news.para: Bank of Communications Co Ltd (BoCom) said it agreed to provide a 100 billion yuan ($13.98 billion) line of credit to Vanke and a 20 billion yuan line of credit to Midea Real Estate Holding Ltd, two separate statements issued by the bank said on Wednesday.

news.title: Delhi HC seeks ED's stand on Preeti Chandra's bail plea in money-laundering case
news.para: Appearing before the court on behalf of Chandra, lawyer Adit Pujari said the applicant is a fashion designer and philanthropist, who has been in custody since October 4, 2021, and there are no proceeds of crime relatable to her.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh: Construction cost up by 20% in two years
news.para: A builder Saurabh Mishra said, “There has been 15 to 20% rise in construction cost in the last couple of years. The cost of iron rod (sariya) has gone up from Rs 52 to Rs 83 per kg after the Russia-Ukraine war. The cost of cement has also gone up by 30% than pre-Covid days.

news.title: Parking spaces in 60% of apartments in Bhubaneswar being misused
news.para: On Monday, the BMC came up with a stricture that if parking norms are not followed within a month of issue of the notice, the establishment will be sealed.
